. Achieving substantive democracy for Ontario’s women, she contends, requires more than just institutional reforms – it demands “femocratic administration” that transforms the entire public service and its relationship with citizens.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aFeminismxPolitical aspectsxOntario. 0aFeminismxPolitical aspectszOntario. 0aWomen and democracyxOntario. 0aWomen and democracyzOntario. 0aWomenxGovernment policyxOntario. 0aWomenxGovernment policyzOntario. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311060681240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144261911140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442619111423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442619111.jpg  a978-3-11-060681-2  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles